title: Alito says he has a ‘pretty good idea’ who leaked draft of abortion opinion
description: Supreme Court Justice Samuel Alito has said that he thinks he knows who leaked his draft opinion to overturn Roe v. Wade in May 2022.

title: Biden meets with top donors as campaign courts deep-pocketed Democrats
description: Some of the biggest Democratic donors gathered in Washington on Friday night for a rare opportunity: face time with President Joe Biden.

title: 5 dead, including child, following shooting at Texas home; suspect at large
description: A suspect is at large following a shooting Friday night at a home in Cleveland, Texas, that left five people, including an 8-year-old child, dead, authorities said.

title: With car repossessions and home foreclosures rising, some Americans are living on a financial cliff
description: A growing number of Americans have found themselves confronting financial hardship as the U.S. economy slows down.

title: Eating disorders among teens more severe than ever, new research indicates
description: Teen eating disorders like anorexia or bulimia have never been this rampant — or this severe, new research indicates.

title: Deepfake porn booms in the age of A.I.
description: A new use of technology in the age of artificial intelligence has led to the disturbing trend of deepfake porn, which takes someone’s face and places it in another’s body without consent.

title: One teen dies after alleged Benadryl social media challenge
description: One teenager has died and another was rushed to a hospital after the families say they ingested large doses of Benadryl for what is known as the Benadryl challenge. NBC’s Maya Eaglin has more on what parents need to know about this years-old social media trend.

title: Montana becomes latest state to ban gender-affirming care for transgender minors
description: Republican Gov. Greg Gianforte signed legislation that exiled transgender lawmaker Zooey Zephyr told fellow lawmakers would leave “blood” on their hands.

title: Army grounds most aviation after fatal helicopter crashes
description: Army leadership on Friday ordered aviation to stand down after two fatal helicopter crashes, the most recent of which killed three soldiers  in Alaska.
